The paper focuses on developer contribution guidelines in social coding sites like GitHub, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) topic. The study also involves analyzing GitHub activity data, which could fall under categories such as cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), software development (cs.SD), and programming languages (cs.PL).
